{"type":"message","id":"38a1f7ab","parentId":"9c3ee04a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:27:32.446Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9wgzudhilw8s_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 3071\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1065\n[mutation proposed] research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\n[master 84376ed] pulse: 2026-03-24 132716\n 6 files changed, 195 insertions(+), 134 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 132716.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 132716.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 132616.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 132716 - The CFI compression synthesis identified that hybrid scoring (CFI x freq) is the next experiment, but the specific scoring formula and evaluation methodology hasn't been designed yet.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tidal-prairie","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 3071\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1065\n[mutation proposed] research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\n[master 84376ed] pulse: 2026-03-24 132716\n 6 files changed, 195 insertions(+), 134 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 132716.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 132716.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 132616.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 132716 - The CFI compression synthesis identified that hybrid scoring (CFI x freq) is the next experiment, but the specific scoring formula and evaluation methodology hasn't been designed yet.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774373252442}}
{"type":"message","id":"75bc67e1","parentId":"38a1f7ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:27:32.450Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9wgzudhilw8s_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 132616\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_HYBRID_SCORING.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and recent progress to determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- The CFI Compression Experiment was just completed, showing CFI gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n- Key finding: CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive\r\n- NEW INSIGHT: Constant Format Problem - tokens like \"for next instantiation\" with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts, not information\r\n- Proposed solution: THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe pending action is: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is:\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists and what needs to be done:\r\n\r\n1. We have pulse data in `data/pulses/` \r\n2. We have analysis in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\r\n3. We need to implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n\r\nThe concrete action should be to implement Strategy C (Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) and run it against the existing data. This involves:\r\n1. Creating a script to compute the hybrid score\r\n2. Running it on the existing 200 pulses\r\n3. Comparing results to the binary threshold approach\r\n\r\nLet me implement this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Experiment identified that \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content. The solution is a hybrid scoring function, but it hasn't been implemented and tested yet.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement the hybrid scoring experiment (Strategy C) defined in the synthesis: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). Create a Python script to test this against the existing 200-pulse dataset and compare precision/recall against the binary threshold approach.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\nBased on CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings\r\n\r\nKey insight: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\nCombines CFI (prediction confidence) with frequency (empirical distribution)\r\nFilters out:\r\n  - Low CFI: random/informational tokens\r\n  - Low freq: rare/noise tokens  \r\n  - High freq ≥120: constant format metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom collections import Counter, defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi(tokens_by_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute Conditional Frequency of Instantiation for each token.\"\"\"\r\n    total_pulses = len(tokens_by_pulse)\r\n    token_instantiation_count = Counter()\r\n    token_total_count = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for tokens in tokens_by_pulse:\r\n        seen_in_pulse = set()\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            token_total_count[token] += 1\r\n            if token not in seen_in_pulse:\r\n                token_instantiation_count[token] += 1\r\n                seen_in_pulse.add(token)\r\n    \r\n    cfi = {}\r\n    for token in token_total_count:\r\n        cfi[token] = token_instantiation_count[token] / total_pulses\r\n    \r\n    return cfi, token_total_count\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq, decay_rate=1/120):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute hybrid score: CFI × min(1, freq/120)\"\"\"\r\n    freq_factor = min(1.0, freq * decay_rate)\r\n    return cfi * freq_factor\r\n\r\ndef binary_threshold_filter(token_data, cfi_thresh=0.5, freq_min=3, freq_max=120):\r\n    \"\"\"Binary threshold approach from synthesis.\"\"\"\r\n    results = []\r\n    for token, (cfi_val, freq_val) in token_data.items():\r\n        if cfi_val >= cfi_thresh and freq_min <= freq_val < freq_max:\r\n            results.append((token, cfi_val, freq_val, cfi_val))\r\n    return results\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_filter(token_data, decay_rate=1/120, score_thresh=0.3):\r\n    \"\"\"Hybrid scoring approach (Strategy C).\"\"\"\r\n    results = []\r\n    for token, (cfi_val, freq_val) in token_data.items():\r\n        score = hybrid_score(cfi_val, freq_val, decay_rate)\r\n        if score >= score_thresh:\r\n            results.append((token, cfi_val, freq_val, score))\r\n    return results\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    pulse_dir = Path(\"data/pulses\")\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Loading {len(pulse_files)} pulses...\")\r\n    tokens_by_pulse = []\r\n    \r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        with open(pf, 'r') as f:\r\n            content = f.read()\r\n        # Tokenize by whitespace\r\n        tokens = content.split()\r\n        tokens_by_pulse.append(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    # Compute CFI and frequency\r\n    print(\"Computing CFI and frequency...\")\r\n    cfi, freq = compute_cfi(tokens_by_pulse)\r\n    \r\n    # Build token data\r\n    token_data = {token: (cfi[token], freq[token]) for token in cfi}\r\n    \r\n    # Run binary threshold filter (baseline)\r\n    binary_results = binary_threshold_filter(token_data)\r\n    binary_results.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])  # Sort by\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:26:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774373252446}}
