{"type":"message","id":"8e4414a4","parentId":"57910c5c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:27:52.327Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mcs5x7uwg4aa_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 132716\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and the recent work:\r\n1. CFI Compression Experiment is complete\r\n2. Key finding: Three-dimensional filter needed - CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n3. Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n4. Also need to distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step from the Pending section is:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe notes say:\r\n- \"Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete\": score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis is essentially the hybrid scoring approach. Let me look at the existing CFI compression research to understand what's already been done and design the next experiment.\r\n\r\nI should create a concrete experiment plan for the hybrid scoring approach, or implement it to run against the pulse data.\r\n\r\nLooking at the files:\r\n- research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md - has the full experiment\r\n\r\nThe most specific next action would be to:\r\n1. Create a design/spec for the hybrid scoring experiment, OR\r\n2. Implement the hybrid scoring and run it\r\n\r\nGiven that the synthesis doc exists and has all the data, the most useful next step is to design the hybrid scoring experiment in detail or implement it.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment plan for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that hybrid scoring (CFI × freq) is the next experiment, but the specific scoring formula and evaluation methodology hasn't been designed yet.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a detailed experiment specification for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring approach, building on the three-dimensional filter finding and the proposed scoring formula.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCombining CFI and frequency multiplicatively (rather than binary thresholds) will:\r\n- Preserve high-CFI tokens that appear moderately often (research trajectory)\r\n- Naturally downweight constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.00)\r\n- Avoid the recall collapse seen in pure CFI≥0.7 filtering (+32.9% precision, -92.9% recall)\r\n\r\n## Proposed Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T) / 120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Experiment Design\r\n1. **Baseline**: Binary CFI≥0.7 threshold (from prior experiment: +32.9% precision, -92.9% recall)\r\n2. **Strategy A**: Binary three-dim filter (CFI≥0.5 AND freq∈[3,120))\r\n3. **Strategy B (NEW)**: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring with top-N selection\r\n4. **Strategy C (NEW)**: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring with adaptive threshold\r\n\r\n## Metrics to Track\r\n- Precision@N (relevance of selected tokens)\r\n- Recall@N (coverage of true causal tokens)\r\n- F1@N (harmonic mean)\r\n- Special: distinguish \"constant format\" vs \"research trajectory\" tokens\r\n\r\n## Data Source\r\nSame 200 pulses (160 train / 40 test split) used in prior CFI experiment.\r\n```\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:27:31\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774373272323}}
